rules: Rule1: If John has health insurance with a health plan, then he achieves financial health.
Rule2: Either John has a personal loan or, provided that he reads diet books, he follows a nutrition plan.
Rule3: Whenever John receives a salary bonus, he buys healthy food.
Rule4: John receives a salary bonus or John receives investment income.
Rule5: Under the condition that John receives investment income, he achieves financial health.
Rule6: Provided that John tracks expenses, he has credit card debt.
Rule7: If John uses a budget app, then whenever he receives a salary bonus, he achieves financial health.
Rule8: Since John is committed to wellness, if he buys healthy food, then he achieves financial health.
Rule9: John has a premium credit card or John has health insurance with a health plan.
Rule10: If John exercises regularly, then it is not the case that he eats junk food.
Rule11: Provided that John meditates daily, he does not eat junk food.
Rule12: Whenever John is stressed about finances, he is anxious about money.
Rule13: Under the condition that John misses a payment deadline, he incurs a late fee.
Rule14: Provided that John incurs a late fee, he does not face a financial penalty.
Rule15: If John reviews the budget, then whenever he monitors spending, either he tracks expenses or he uses a budget app.
Rule16: Under the condition that John invests in the stock market, he has high-risk investments.
Rule17: Either John invests in the stock market or John does not have a premium credit card.
Rule18: Since John follows a nutrition plan, if he shops at a health store, then he can afford organic food.
Rule19: If John consults a nutritionist, then he reads diet books.
Rule20: If it is not the case that receiving a salary bonus leads to achieving financial health, then John faces a financial penalty.
Rule21: Provided that it is false that receiving a salary bonus implies achieving financial health, John misses a payment deadline.
Rule22: Whenever it is not the case that either John tracks expenses or uses a budget app, he overspends monthly.
Rule23: If it is not the case that either John exercises regularly or meditates daily, then he is stressed about finances.
Rule24: Provided that it is false that planning for retirement implies not neglecting finances, John is worried about the future.
Rule25: If it is not the case that not tracking expenses or using a budget app implies not overspending monthly, then John saves money monthly.
Rule26: Under the condition that it is false that not tracking expenses or using a budget app leads to not overspending monthly, John does not save money monthly.
Rule27: If John is not committed to wellness, then he eats junk food.
Rule28: Provided that John does not review the budget, he neglects finances.
Rule29: Whenever John does not achieve financial health, he shops at a health store.
facts: Fact4: John does not have a personal loan.
Fact5: John does not have credit card debt.
Fact6: John is not anxious about money.
Fact7: John is not worried about the future.
Fact8: John does not have high-risk investments.
Fact9: John cannot afford organic food.
